      </transcription>
      <translation>
         <line n="a1">
            <tr>/// [full-mouthed], ovine, 1. The <hi>saṃgha</hi> ate (it). <hi>Jñāṇavire</hi> the <hi>Pañcwarike</hi> monk has seen [it]. Then, <hi>Räktāśka</hi> took the meat of 1 female new-born, 1 female goat kid, (and) 1 male goat kid. Women ate (them). <hi>Śilawratti</hi> the <hi>Yotkolau</hi> gave to them. </tr>
         </line>
